<title>The Sociological Eye: Learning about Society and Culture through Films</title>
<course_type>Lecture</course_type>
<course_level code="O">For Undergraduates and Graduates</course_level>
<credit code="1">Half course</credit>
<meeting_text>Tu., Th., at 1</meeting_text>
<faculty_text>Alvaro Agustin Santana Acuna</faculty_text>
<description>This course introduces students to key themes, methods, and concepts in social and cultural analysis through a global selection of classic and contemporary films, documentaries, and TV series. Topics and related readings cover social control, identity, deviance, power, commodification, stigma, networks and stratification, among others. Screenings include House of Cards, Avatar, The Matrix, "The Wire," Psycho, King Kong, and The Social Network, among others.</description>
